1
00:01:20,073 --> 00:01:20,937
Hello.

2
00:01:21,608 --> 00:01:22,939
Why don't you answer?

3
00:01:26,813 --> 00:01:27,780
Get out of there!

4
00:01:29,916 --> 00:01:32,077
Um, I don't...

5
00:01:32,218 --> 00:01:33,879
They'll...your leg...

6
00:01:39,492 --> 00:01:40,322
''Out of Range''

7
00:01:41,861 --> 00:01:43,385
Get away!

8
00:01:43,530 --> 00:01:45,259
They'll cut off your leg!

9
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,357
''Ashikari, Help!''

10
00:04:24,791 --> 00:04:30,229
''X-CROSS''

11
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:43,709
Hello? Hey, how are you?

12
00:04:45,878 --> 00:04:47,743
I'm heading to
the hot springs with a friend.

13
00:04:48,548 --> 00:04:50,243
''Chapter One''

14
00:04:50,383 --> 00:04:54,479
''The white cell phone,
in the closet.''

15
00:04:56,522 --> 00:04:59,389
Oh, really? Too bad.
Invite me again sometime.

16
00:05:03,062 --> 00:05:05,326
Yeah, yeah.

17
00:05:05,465 --> 00:05:06,454
Bye.

18
00:05:11,904 --> 00:05:15,431
Hey, are you sure
this is the right road?

19
00:05:15,575 --> 00:05:17,042
I don't know, probably.

20
00:05:17,176 --> 00:05:20,236
What do you mean ''probably''?
Read the map!

21
00:05:21,447 --> 00:05:23,881
Shiyori, Blood type A,
Luckiest week for love.

22
00:05:24,017 --> 00:05:27,418
You may meet your soul mate.
Go for it!

23
00:05:27,553 --> 00:05:30,545
Blood type B...
''Watch for stalkers''?

24
00:05:30,690 --> 00:05:31,952
Oh, too bad.

25
00:05:34,394 --> 00:05:37,625
Exactly how many guys
are you dating, Aiko?

26
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:42,567
Three...No, make that four.

27
00:05:43,169 --> 00:05:47,196
Are you really in love
with all of them?

28
00:05:47,974 --> 00:05:50,067
Well, I guess, sort of.

29
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:52,507
''Sort of'?

30
00:05:52,645 --> 00:05:56,206
I don't want to get hurt
the way you did.

31
00:05:58,384 --> 00:05:59,510
Meaning?

32
00:05:59,652 --> 00:06:02,712
''Sort of' is better to
not get hurt.

33
00:06:02,855 --> 00:06:06,450
Keep a certain distance
and nobody gets hurt.

34
00:06:17,470 --> 00:06:18,732
Is that true for me, too?

35
00:06:20,239 --> 00:06:21,103
What?

36
00:06:23,076 --> 00:06:27,445
Am I just a ''sort of' friend
to you?

37
00:06:31,617 --> 00:06:34,643
Hey, don't get all serious on me.

38
00:06:38,024 --> 00:06:39,048
Watch out!

39
00:06:48,401 --> 00:06:49,368
Ouch...

40
00:06:56,008 --> 00:06:58,306
Hey, what are you doing?

41
00:07:03,516 --> 00:07:05,643
Snip, snip, snip...

42
00:07:08,654 --> 00:07:10,747
Snip, snip, snip...

43
00:07:12,692 --> 00:07:13,784
Hell.

44
00:07:18,097 --> 00:07:21,157
Have you ever seen
the true face...

45
00:07:22,435 --> 00:07:24,460
of hell?

46
00:07:36,649 --> 00:07:38,879
Snip, snip, snip...

47
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:29,394
Hey, the reception here sucks!

48
00:08:29,535 --> 00:08:30,968
How's yours, Shiyori?

49
00:08:37,877 --> 00:08:39,538
Mine's out of range, too.

50
00:08:42,648 --> 00:08:43,580
Here's a map.

51
00:08:46,018 --> 00:08:47,212
We're here now.

52
00:08:47,954 --> 00:08:50,252
-The inn?
-Here?

53
00:08:50,389 --> 00:08:51,413
The baths!

54
00:08:51,557 --> 00:08:55,755
It's still a long way to the inn.
How will we get there?

55
00:08:57,029 --> 00:08:58,792
What'll we do?

56
00:09:07,807 --> 00:09:08,637
Hello?

57
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,881
You're guests at
the hot springs inn?

58
00:09:19,719 --> 00:09:22,381
Welcome to Ashikari village.

59
00:09:23,155 --> 00:09:25,385
Please, get in the car.

60
00:09:26,993 --> 00:09:28,085
Please, please.

61
00:09:30,463 --> 00:09:31,293
Let's go.

62
00:09:35,935 --> 00:09:37,197
Don't be shy.

63
00:09:39,505 --> 00:09:40,938
Welcome, welcome.

64
00:09:41,941 --> 00:09:43,772
Thank you for coming
such a long way to visit us.

65
00:09:44,877 --> 00:09:45,969
Welcome.

66
00:10:04,096 --> 00:10:07,031
''Welcome to Ashikari village''

67
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:45,027
Thank you for visiting us.

68
00:10:45,771 --> 00:10:49,298
This is a pretty fancy inn
for the middle of nowhere.

69
00:10:51,077 --> 00:10:56,071
All the villagers built it
together to welcome our guests.

70
00:10:59,985 --> 00:11:01,282
The villagers?

71
00:11:03,522 --> 00:11:06,616
We've been loggers
for generations.

72
00:11:09,362 --> 00:11:13,731
How many people
live in this village?

73
00:11:15,401 --> 00:11:17,995
(Ashikari dialect)

74
00:11:19,972 --> 00:11:20,802
Excuse me?

75
00:11:23,943 --> 00:11:29,643
That's why,
it's just us old folks here now.

76
00:11:37,590 --> 00:11:39,558
''Asamiya Keiichi''

77
00:11:49,535 --> 00:11:52,163
I'll leave
your bathing gowns here.

78
00:11:53,406 --> 00:11:56,534
May I serve dinner
after your bath?

79
00:11:57,376 --> 00:11:58,206
Yes.

80
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:01,711
The hot springs are relaxing.

81
00:12:01,847 --> 00:12:05,408
Please take care to
wash your legs.

82
00:12:27,106 --> 00:12:29,506
We landed in one helluva place.

83
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:40,743
-It didn't matter where...
-What?

84
00:12:42,154 --> 00:12:46,090
So long as
it was far away from him.

85
00:12:48,694 --> 00:12:50,161
Is it really over?

86
00:12:51,931 --> 00:12:54,456
So he cheated on you once.
It's no big deal

87
00:12:57,837 --> 00:12:59,429
You wouldn't understand.

88
00:13:04,410 --> 00:13:05,240
What?

89
00:13:06,879 --> 00:13:10,576
You've never really
cried over anyone.

90
00:13:11,383 --> 00:13:12,941
You date all those guys.

91
00:13:13,886 --> 00:13:16,377
I don't even want you
to understand how I feel.

92
00:13:17,756 --> 00:13:19,724
He was my very first boyfriend.

93
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:25,524
So what?

94
00:13:32,538 --> 00:13:33,903
I'm going back to the room.

95
00:13:54,994 --> 00:13:56,928
Hello, it's me.

96
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:00,021
Shiyori just left the baths.

97
00:14:01,066 --> 00:14:03,899
Yeah, everything's on schedule.

98
00:14:14,914 --> 00:14:18,543
''Shiyori, let's talk.
Please answer. Keiichi''

99
00:15:08,601 --> 00:15:10,034
Shiyori!

100
00:15:12,071 --> 00:15:13,368
Shiyori!

101
00:18:15,754 --> 00:18:16,618
Hello?

102
00:18:17,756 --> 00:18:19,087
Why don't you answer?

103
00:18:23,061 --> 00:18:24,028
Get out of there!

104
00:18:25,164 --> 00:18:27,860
Um, I don't...

105
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:30,025
They'll...your leg...

106
00:18:35,040 --> 00:18:36,871
''From Mononobe Akira''

107
00:18:37,976 --> 00:18:39,500
Get away!

108
00:18:39,645 --> 00:18:41,306
They'll cut off your leg!

109
00:19:10,943 --> 00:19:14,003
How was your bath?

110
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:16,713
Lovely, thank you.

111
00:19:16,849 --> 00:19:20,717
Please eat your dinner
while it's hot.

112
00:19:21,553 --> 00:19:25,421
Call me on the house phone
when you finished the dinner.

113
00:19:25,557 --> 00:19:26,785
Thank you.

114
00:20:18,343 --> 00:20:19,173
Hello?

115
00:20:19,778 --> 00:20:22,212
What's wrong? What happened?

116
00:20:23,949 --> 00:20:25,246
No, not really.

117
00:20:25,984 --> 00:20:27,178
Get out of there now!

118
00:20:27,986 --> 00:20:30,716
If they catch you,
they'll sacrifice you.

119
00:20:31,890 --> 00:20:34,222
Is this a prank call?

120
00:20:35,394 --> 00:20:38,488
This isn't even my cell phone.

121
00:20:42,601 --> 00:20:43,966
Who are you?

122
00:20:44,102 --> 00:20:45,660
I am...

123
00:20:45,804 --> 00:20:46,828
You're not Shizuka?

124
00:20:46,972 --> 00:20:48,234
No, I'm not.

125
00:20:48,373 --> 00:20:52,309
Why, why do you have
my sister's phone?

126
00:20:52,444 --> 00:20:54,935
I'm staying here with my friend.

127
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:58,572
I found this cell phone
in the closet.

128
00:20:58,717 --> 00:20:59,684
Oh, no...

129
00:21:02,154 --> 00:21:04,486
Don't tell me Shizuka's already...

130
00:21:20,072 --> 00:21:22,540
-What is this?
-What happened?

131
00:21:24,109 --> 00:21:26,373
Suddenly, all the lights went out.

132
00:21:27,446 --> 00:21:30,813
I get it. They've finally done it.

133
00:21:32,951 --> 00:21:34,111
Who's they?

134
00:21:34,786 --> 00:21:37,414
Who are you? What's going on?

135
00:21:56,141 --> 00:22:00,635
Dear guest,
have you cleaned your leg?

136
00:22:01,446 --> 00:22:04,779
About the power failure,
there's no need to worry.

137
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:08,114
I'll be there right away.

138
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:11,411
Don't bother, I'm going to bed!

139
00:22:14,459 --> 00:22:17,792
What did you mean when
you said they'd sacrifice me?

140
00:22:19,297 --> 00:22:23,791
I'm not sure you're going
to believe what I have to say.

141
00:22:23,935 --> 00:22:25,425
Go ahead, tell me.

142
00:22:26,805 --> 00:22:29,239
I'm Mononobe Akira.

143
00:22:30,675 --> 00:22:34,406
I'm researching folklore
at Jonan University.

144
00:22:37,115 --> 00:22:39,174
-Folklore?
-Yes.

145
00:22:40,085 --> 00:22:43,316
In ancient Japan,

146
00:22:44,156 --> 00:22:46,317
they used to sacrifice
young women,

147
00:22:47,426 --> 00:22:50,156
in order to ward off disasters.

148
00:22:52,764 --> 00:22:56,097
They used to in Ashikari village,
where you are now.

149
00:23:23,361 --> 00:23:27,127
Originally, Ashikari was
a loggers' village.

150
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:32,064
In order to prevent their wives
from fleeing the village...

151
00:23:33,138 --> 00:23:35,333
while the men were cutting
down trees in the mountains,

152
00:23:36,575 --> 00:23:39,476
they cut off
their wives' left legs.

153
00:23:43,048 --> 00:23:45,539
That's how this grim
tradition began.

154
00:23:49,554 --> 00:23:53,354
Eventually, the villagers captured
traveling women,

155
00:23:54,459 --> 00:23:57,292
offering them as living sacrifice
to the mountains.

156
00:24:11,710 --> 00:24:13,371
The sacrificed women...

157
00:24:14,212 --> 00:24:18,114
were locked up in a shrine
on the mountain.

158
00:24:19,584 --> 00:24:23,953
To this day, they've secretly
kept the tradition alive.

159
00:24:26,558 --> 00:24:28,890
You've seen how
all the villagers limp?

160
00:24:30,328 --> 00:24:33,957
As soon as a baby is born, they
cut the tendons in the left leg.

161
00:24:34,866 --> 00:24:36,163
To brand them...

162
00:24:37,035 --> 00:24:38,935
and to keep them
from running away.

163
00:25:00,158 --> 00:25:01,216
lmpossible!

164
00:25:02,394 --> 00:25:04,123
I know you
don't want to believe it.

165
00:25:05,564 --> 00:25:07,191
But you saw for yourself.

166
00:25:08,366 --> 00:25:10,630
All the scarecrows
around the village.

167
00:25:13,572 --> 00:25:14,903
They're not decorations.

168
00:25:16,274 --> 00:25:18,174
They're mummies of the dead women,

169
00:25:18,777 --> 00:25:20,768
worshiped as gods.

170
00:25:25,317 --> 00:25:28,286
Watch out!
The rituaI's already begun!

171
00:25:57,249 --> 00:25:58,511
Oh, goddess!

172
00:26:05,156 --> 00:26:07,716
I've brought you a light.

173
00:26:07,859 --> 00:26:10,692
It's dangerous in the dark.

174
00:26:13,064 --> 00:26:14,088
Dear guest.

175
00:26:14,232 --> 00:26:16,200
What's going on?

176
00:26:17,836 --> 00:26:20,100
Hello? hello?

177
00:26:21,039 --> 00:26:21,869
Hello.

178
00:26:23,408 --> 00:26:24,705
Please tell me your name.

179
00:26:27,012 --> 00:26:29,344
I'm Mizuno Shiyori.

180
00:26:30,015 --> 00:26:30,947
Shiyori.

181
00:26:33,551 --> 00:26:34,677
I want to help you.

182
00:26:36,321 --> 00:26:40,223
Either you believe what I told you
or they cut your leg off?

183
00:26:41,192 --> 00:26:42,955
The choice is yours.

184
00:26:47,565 --> 00:26:50,295
Hello, hello, Mononobe!

185
00:26:50,435 --> 00:26:51,800
Please, wait!

186
00:26:52,971 --> 00:26:54,529
Are you all right?

187
00:26:55,840 --> 00:26:59,776
If you won't open the door,
I'm coming in.

188
00:27:35,347 --> 00:27:36,405
Not this one.

189
00:27:40,151 --> 00:27:42,312
Why don't you answer, Aiko?

190
00:28:13,852 --> 00:28:17,288
''It's awful! Contact me now.
Shiyori''

191
00:28:36,141 --> 00:28:39,304
Please, Aiko, answer! Please!

192
00:28:41,679 --> 00:28:43,806
''Incoming EmaiI''

193
00:28:44,682 --> 00:28:47,116
''Help! Waiting in the toilet
by the bath. Aiko.''

194
00:28:52,056 --> 00:28:54,251
-Mononobe!
-Where are you?

195
00:28:54,826 --> 00:28:57,021
I escaped from the lodge.

196
00:28:57,162 --> 00:28:58,789
Did you bring the village map?

197
00:28:58,930 --> 00:28:59,760
Yes.

198
00:29:03,935 --> 00:29:07,166
They'll have shut all
the main roads down by now.

199
00:29:08,039 --> 00:29:11,133
It's a little far but there's
an old tunnel on the east side.

200
00:29:13,378 --> 00:29:17,075
Wait for me there.
I'm driving towards you now.

201
00:29:18,049 --> 00:29:18,947
I understand.

202
00:29:19,884 --> 00:29:23,251
By the way,
I have an important question.

203
00:29:25,123 --> 00:29:27,614
How did you learn about
Ashikari village?

204
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:32,428
A friend of mine from school...
Her name's Aiko.

205
00:29:33,031 --> 00:29:35,795
She invited me
to the hot springs here.

206
00:29:37,769 --> 00:29:40,897
I've got to go help her.

207
00:29:41,906 --> 00:29:43,635
How did she
learn about the village?

208
00:29:45,243 --> 00:29:46,676
On the Internet, she said.

209
00:29:47,612 --> 00:29:48,636
I doubt it.

210
00:29:51,149 --> 00:29:52,673
According to my research,

211
00:29:52,817 --> 00:29:57,254
there's nothing on the Internet
about Ashikari village.

212
00:29:59,591 --> 00:30:03,618
Oh, no, then Aiko's...

213
00:30:04,395 --> 00:30:06,192
She may be one of them.

214
00:30:21,713 --> 00:30:22,839
Hello?

215
00:30:22,981 --> 00:30:24,710
Listen, Shiyori.

216
00:30:26,217 --> 00:30:28,583
You've got to get out alive.

217
00:30:30,121 --> 00:30:31,213
If you want to survive,

218
00:30:32,023 --> 00:30:35,220
don't trust anyone or anything.

219
00:30:38,630 --> 00:30:41,463
Hello, hello!

220
00:32:31,075 --> 00:32:32,099
Aiko.

221
00:32:44,722 --> 00:32:45,814
Please...

222
00:32:46,557 --> 00:32:48,115
Answer, Aiko.

223
00:32:53,464 --> 00:32:54,795
Please.

224
00:32:54,932 --> 00:32:55,990
Hello?

225
00:32:56,134 --> 00:33:00,070
Hello, Aiko!
Thank god you're okay.

226
00:33:00,204 --> 00:33:01,762
I was so worried.

227
00:33:02,373 --> 00:33:05,604
Shiyori, what phone
are you calling from?

228
00:33:05,743 --> 00:33:09,509
I'll tell you later!
Tell me, where are you?

229
00:33:12,016 --> 00:33:12,880
In the toilet.

230
00:33:13,451 --> 00:33:16,011
What? But I'm in the toilet.

231
00:33:17,188 --> 00:33:20,282
You're in a different toilet.

232
00:33:31,536 --> 00:33:34,596
Just watch out for the villagers.

233
00:33:36,040 --> 00:33:39,066
This village is like sicko!

234
00:33:43,247 --> 00:33:45,340
-Aiko...
-What?

235
00:33:48,352 --> 00:33:51,810
You're not tricking me, are you?

236
00:33:53,057 --> 00:33:54,183
What do you mean?

237
00:33:55,860 --> 00:34:00,160
I can really trust you, right?

238
00:34:07,405 --> 00:34:08,429
Answer me.

239
00:34:09,607 --> 00:34:12,440
Why can't you answer! Aiko!

240
00:34:14,245 --> 00:34:18,409
Listen, Shiyori. The truth is...

241
00:34:22,086 --> 00:34:24,554
Hello, Aiko, Aiko!

242
00:34:24,689 --> 00:34:27,123
What's wrong! Hello!

243
00:35:20,178 --> 00:35:21,202
Aiko?

244
00:35:33,891 --> 00:35:34,721
Hello?

245
00:35:34,859 --> 00:35:35,757
Yayoi?

246
00:35:37,461 --> 00:35:38,689
What, Shiyori?

247
00:35:40,164 --> 00:35:43,656
Thank god, I got through!

248
00:35:43,801 --> 00:35:45,894
You're my only friend.

249
00:35:46,771 --> 00:35:48,830
Please, Yayoi, help me.

250
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:50,732
What's going on?

251
00:35:53,578 --> 00:35:56,445
''Ashikari village''

252
00:35:57,114 --> 00:35:59,105
''No Matching Documents''

253
00:35:59,250 --> 00:36:02,310
That guy, Mononobe's story
does make sense.

254
00:36:03,654 --> 00:36:08,353
But there's no proof that
you can trust him either.

255
00:36:09,994 --> 00:36:11,723
And the cell phone you're using,

256
00:36:12,330 --> 00:36:15,458
we don't even know
if there really is a Shizuka.

257
00:36:16,334 --> 00:36:17,596
But...

258
00:36:17,735 --> 00:36:21,193
In any case, I'll call the police.

259
00:36:21,339 --> 00:36:23,773
And I'll check out
this guy Mononobe.

260
00:36:23,908 --> 00:36:24,897
Thank you.

261
00:36:25,810 --> 00:36:27,437
And I don't like saying this...

262
00:36:30,047 --> 00:36:31,571
but...watch out for Aiko.

263
00:36:34,685 --> 00:36:37,620
What's that supposed to mean?

264
00:36:38,756 --> 00:36:40,417
She's just not my type.

265
00:36:41,092 --> 00:36:43,026
Frankly, I don't trust her.

266
00:36:49,333 --> 00:36:51,164
You're too trusting.

267
00:36:52,336 --> 00:36:54,736
People take advantage of you.

268
00:36:55,406 --> 00:36:57,840
But believe in yourself
and don't give up.

269
00:36:59,143 --> 00:37:01,441
I wish I could go help you.

270
00:37:03,581 --> 00:37:05,913
